# <<REPO_NAME>> — environment configuration
#
# Template — copy to `<<REPO_NAME>>/.env.example` and replace every
# `<<TOKEN>>` placeholder. The file should remain comment-only when the
# repo reads no env vars at runtime; add `KEY=` lines (with no value) when
# real vars are required. Closes the `env_template` Agent-Readiness
# criterion.
#
# Operators copy this file to `.env` and fill values:
#
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# `.env` itself is gitignored (see `.gitignore`). `.env.example` is
# committed and tracked — keep it in sync with whatever the runtime
# actually reads.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# How to use this template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# 1. If `<<REPO_NAME>>` reads NO env vars (most CLI libraries):
#    Keep the file comment-only. Replace the "Required" / "Optional"
#    sections below with a single line:
#
#        # <<REPO_NAME>> does not read environment variables at runtime.
#        # This file exists so contributors know the convention applies.
#
# 2. If `<<REPO_NAME>>` reads env vars, group them by lifecycle:
#    - Required at boot (the process refuses to start without them).
#    - Optional with defaults (document the default in the comment).
#    - Provider tokens (separate section so secret-scanning tools can
#      target them).
#
# 3. Never commit a real value. Use empty `KEY=` or a placeholder like
#    `<your-token-here>`. Document how to generate (e.g.
#    `openssl rand -hex 32`).
#
# 4. Mirror this file into AGENTS.md or the README under an
#    "Environment variables" section so a new contributor finds it.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# # <<EXAMPLE_KEY>>
# # What the variable controls. Why it is required. How to generate or
# # obtain a value (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`, "your Anthropic dashboard").
# <<EXAMPLE_KEY>>=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional (with defaults)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# # <<OPTIONAL_KEY>>
# # What it tunes. Default: <<DEFAULT_VALUE>>. Acceptable range / values.
# <<OPTIONAL_KEY>>=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Provider tokens (kept in a dedicated section for secret-scanning hooks)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# # <<PROVIDER_TOKEN>>
# # Where the token reaches. Scope required. How to rotate.
# <<PROVIDER_TOKEN>>=
